cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL

This paper deals with predicting the popularity of news items on social media, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques to extract features from news articles, which suggests the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as likely candidates. Additionally, the paper deals with analyzing and modeling data, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
